# Rust
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock is committed: the workspace ships a bin (crates/fprintd), and distro packaging and
# hardware runs need the exact graph docs/known-issues.md's pins were reasoned about.

# What a fuzz campaign generates. `fuzz/` is its own workspace (see its Cargo.toml), and its
# corpus and findings are reproducible from the seeds and the targets — what survives a campaign is
# the frozen counterexample under crates/*/tests/regressions/, not the corpus that found it.
# Listed here rather than in a fuzz/.gitignore so that `reuse lint`, which reads this file, agrees
# with git about what is generated.
/fuzz/target/
/fuzz/corpus/
/fuzz/artifacts/
/fuzz/coverage/

# What a mutation run generates (`mise run mutants`). Same reasoning as the fuzz corpus: what the
# run finds is a missing test, and a missing test is committed as a test — the report it was found
# in is reproducible from the tree and .cargo/mutants.toml.
/mutants.out/
/mutants.out.old/

# The compilation cache CI carries between runs (docker/docker-compose.ci.yml). Only the `linux`
# job mounts it; a dev box never creates it.
/.sccache/

# Upstream references cloned for reading/measurement (populate via `mise run clone-ref`)
/reference/

# mise local overrides
/mise.local.toml
/.mise.local.toml

# Editor / OS
/.idea/
/.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
